WEBVTT

00:13.210 --> 00:15.007
WHAT DOES
THE OMNIBUS CRIME CONTROL

00:15.010 --> 00:16.546
AND SAFE STREETS ACT
MAKE ILLEGAL?

00:16.550 --> 00:19.769
ELECTRONIC SURVEILLANCE
WITHOUT JUDICIAL AUTHORIZATION.

00:21.220 --> 00:23.211
WHAT WAS THAT?

00:23.220 --> 00:25.848
I'M TAKING
MY P.I. EXAM TOMORROW.

00:25.850 --> 00:27.351
HE'S ENSURING HIS LEGACY.

00:27.360 --> 00:30.079
HE'S NERVOUS FOR YOU.
THAT'S SWEET.

00:30.090 --> 00:31.887
HE SHOULD BE NERVOUS
FOR HIMSELF.

00:31.890 --> 00:33.494
I'M GONNA BEAT HIS SCORE.

00:33.500 --> 00:36.822
THEN I'M GONNA DINE ON THAT
SHARED KNOWLEDGE FOR A LIFETIME.

00:36.830 --> 00:40.391
A PASSIVE INFRARED DETECTOR
WOULD NOT BE THE BEST CHOICE

00:40.400 --> 00:42.834
UNDER WHICH OF THE FOLLOWING
CONDITIONS --

00:42.840 --> 00:44.398
"A," OVERHEAD DOORS,

00:44.410 --> 00:47.299
"B," SIGNIFICANT CHANGES
IN TEMPERATURE, "C" --

00:47.310 --> 00:50.199
"B." WHY DON'T YOU BUG PIZ
FOR A WHILE?

00:50.210 --> 00:52.815
SO, PIZ,
WHAT ARE YOU STUDYING?

00:54.780 --> 00:55.872
APOLLO --

00:55.880 --> 00:57.108
BU KENYA.

00:57.120 --> 00:58.781
YEAH, HE ACTUALLY
GOES TO HEARST,

00:58.790 --> 01:02.351
AND HE WROTE THIS, UH, MEMOIR,
I GUESS YOU'D CALL IT.

01:02.360 --> 01:04.419
WHAT COULD A COLLEGE KID
POSSIBLY HAVE

01:04.430 --> 01:06.022
TO PUT IN A MEMOIR?

01:06.030 --> 01:08.419
[ Chuckling ] SURVIVING
SPRING BREAK ON 10 BUCKS A DAY?

01:08.430 --> 01:10.990
HE WAS A CHILD SOLDIER
IN UGANDA.

01:11.000 --> 01:12.763
HE NEVER KNEW HIS FATHER.

01:12.770 --> 01:15.796
THE REBEL ARMY PUT A GUN IN HIS
HAND WHEN HE WAS 6 YEARS OLD.

01:15.800 --> 01:17.233
OH.

01:17.240 --> 01:18.434
SOMEHOW HE MANAGED
TO ESCAPE AS A TEENAGER

01:18.440 --> 01:19.930
AND GET TO THE STATES.

01:19.940 --> 01:22.374
I'M INTERVIEWING HIM
ON MY RADIO SHOW TOMORROW.

01:22.380 --> 01:24.940
THE BOOK'S ALREADY
BEEN OPTIONED AS A MOVIE --

01:24.950 --> 01:26.178
MIDDLE SIX FIGURES.

01:26.180 --> 01:28.148
PLUS, HE'S BEEN BOOKED
ON "OPRAH,"

01:28.150 --> 01:30.539
BUT PIZ GOT HIM FIRST.

01:32.960 --> 01:34.211
WHAT?

01:34.220 --> 01:35.778
IT'S JUST SO REFRESHING
TO HEAR

01:35.790 --> 01:39.226
ONE OF YOUR GENTLEMAN CALLERS
HAVE MORE TO TALK ABOUT

01:39.230 --> 01:41.357
THAN HOW HIGH
THE WAVES ARE BREAKING.

01:41.360 --> 01:43.225
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

01:43.230 --> 01:45.061
HELLO, HELLO?

01:45.070 --> 01:47.891
UH-OH.

01:47.900 --> 01:49.094
WHAT?

01:49.100 --> 01:51.136
DAD LIKES YOU?
KISS OF DEATH?

01:52.340 --> 01:55.036
WHAT WAS THE ADDRESS?

01:55.040 --> 01:56.439
TWO OF THEM?

01:56.450 --> 01:59.146
WE'VE JUST HAD
OUR SEVENTH HOME BURGLARY

01:59.150 --> 02:01.141
IN THE PAST 13 DAYS.

02:01.150 --> 02:02.845
SEVENTH --

02:02.850 --> 02:06.047
THAT'S WHAT THE PAPERS BEGIN
REFERRING TO AS A CRIME WAVE.

02:06.050 --> 02:07.608
IN SIX OF THE SEVEN,

02:07.620 --> 02:09.986
THE BURGLARS HAVE ALSO
STOLEN CARS FROM THE RESIDENCES.

02:09.990 --> 02:12.857
ALL THE BURGLARIES OCCURRED
IN OUR FAVORITE ZIP CODE.

02:12.860 --> 02:17.593
AS YOU KNOW, THE RESIDENTS...
ARE AN IMPATIENT LOT.

02:17.600 --> 02:19.534
NOW, THE ONE CAR WE RECOVERED

02:19.540 --> 02:22.862
HAD SWITCHED PLATES WITH A CAR
IN A SUPERMARKET PARKING LOT.

02:22.870 --> 02:25.737
JERRY WILL HAND OUT PRINTOUTS
DETAILING THE HOT SPOTS.

02:25.740 --> 02:29.346
STOLEN GOODS
MIGHT START POPPING UP SOON.

02:29.350 --> 02:30.772
KITSITZ, HOROWITZ,

02:30.780 --> 02:33.169
DROP IN ON THE PAWNSHOPS
AND ALL KNOWN FENCES.

02:56.440 --> 02:58.829
Veronica:
THE JOB FAIR HAS EVERYONE HERE

02:58.840 --> 03:00.307
IN A FEEDING FRENZY.

03:00.310 --> 03:02.175
REAL JOBS
FOR OVERACHIEVING SENIORS

03:02.180 --> 03:05.547
AND VOLUNTEER WORK FOR EVERYONE
LOOKING TO FILL A RSUM.

03:05.550 --> 03:07.541
ME, THE JOB I'M WAITING ON,

03:07.550 --> 03:11.179
I WOULD HAVE BEEN BETTER OFF
BUYING A LO'I'I'ERY TICKET.

03:12.560 --> 03:14.551
[ Ugandan accent ]
NOT LONG AFI'ER I ESCAPED,

03:14.560 --> 03:16.585
I WAS AT AN EVAC HOSPITAL,

03:16.590 --> 03:20.697
AND A VERY KINDHEARTED NURSE
WAS TRYING TO COMFORT ME,

03:20.700 --> 03:23.498
TELLING ME THAT WHAT I DID
WAS NOT MY FAULT

03:23.500 --> 03:25.923
BECAUSE I WAS JUST A CHILD.

03:25.930 --> 03:29.661
WHAT I HAVE TO LIVE WITH TODAY
IS THE KNOWLEDGE THAT,

03:29.670 --> 03:31.501
WHEN MY ABDUCTORS COAXED --

03:31.510 --> 03:35.435
OR RATHER, BRAINWASHED ME
INTO AN INSTRUMENT OF VIOLENCE,

03:35.440 --> 03:39.206
I WAS LEFI' WITH
NOT JUST THE ABILITY,

03:39.210 --> 03:41.519
BUT THE APPETITE TO KILL.

03:41.520 --> 03:45.286
Piz: MY GUEST
IS APOLLO BUKENYA,

03:45.290 --> 03:46.917
A HEARST STUDENT

03:46.920 --> 03:49.923
WHO MIRACULOUSLY ESCAPED
THE LRA IN UGANDA.

03:49.930 --> 03:53.422
APOLLO, YOU DEDICATE
"SOLDIER OF MISFORTUNE"

03:53.430 --> 03:55.796
TO YOUR ADVISER
HERE AT HEARST,

03:55.800 --> 03:57.791
PROFESSOR LISA TONIN,
WHO IS HERE WITH US.

03:57.800 --> 03:59.836
I OWE HER A GREAT DEAL
OF GRATITUDE.

03:59.840 --> 04:01.899
THERE WOULD BE NO BOOK
WITHOUT HER.

04:01.900 --> 04:05.165
I UNDERSTAND SHE KNEW YOU
BEFORE YOU CAME TO HEARST.

04:05.170 --> 04:06.808
SHE DID.

04:06.810 --> 04:10.302
SHE ACTUALLY READ A SHORT STORY
I WROTE WHEN I WAS 15

04:10.310 --> 04:11.902
AND CALLED ME.

04:11.910 --> 04:15.016
SHE'S BEEN MY FRIEND AND MENTOR
EVER SINCE.

04:15.020 --> 04:16.385
PROFESSOR TONIN?

04:16.390 --> 04:17.812
WELL, OF COURSE,
I'M FLA'ITERED,

04:17.820 --> 04:20.584
BUT THE TRUTH IS THAT APOLLO
HAS TAUGHT ME

04:20.590 --> 04:23.081
MUCH MORE
THAN I HAVE TAUGHT HIM.

04:23.090 --> 04:24.489
AHH.

04:24.490 --> 04:28.358
YOU REALIZE YOU'RE
THE RADIO-HOST VERSION

04:28.360 --> 04:29.827
OF A ROCK STAR, RIGHT?

04:29.830 --> 04:32.469
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT THE GROUPIE PROCEDURE

04:32.470 --> 04:33.937
IS FOR THIS SCENARIO,

04:33.940 --> 04:36.602
BUT I MIGHT HAVE TO
THROW MY PANTIES AT YOU.

04:36.610 --> 04:38.532
OR I COULD AUTOGRAPH YOU.

04:38.540 --> 04:42.203
I BELIEVE WE HAVE SOME SHARPIES
LAYING AROUND.

04:42.210 --> 04:44.201
SO, I HAVE NEWS.

04:44.880 --> 04:47.474
I GOT OFFERED AN INTERNSHIP
WITH PITCHFORKMEDIA.

04:47.480 --> 04:49.584
IT'S PRETTY MUCH
THE MOST HIGHLY REGARDED

04:49.590 --> 04:51.478
MUSIC-REVIEW PUBLICATION
ON THE INTERNET.

04:51.490 --> 04:53.082
PIZ, THAT'S FANTASTIC!

04:53.090 --> 04:55.149
I'D WORK WITH THE MOST IMPORTANT
CRITICS IN THE BUSINESS,

04:55.160 --> 04:57.526
SEE BANDS WHEN THEY'RE
ON THE VERGE OF BREAKING,

04:57.530 --> 04:59.521
MIGHT EVEN GET TO DO
A FEW REVIEWS MYSELF,

04:59.530 --> 05:01.623
SO I CAN REALLY
GET MY SNOB ON.

05:01.630 --> 05:03.621
THEIR OFFICES
ARE IN NEW YORK,

05:03.630 --> 05:06.531
WHICH COULD BE COOL,
RIGHT?

05:06.540 --> 05:09.236
SUPERCOOL,
YOU LUCKY DOG!

05:09.240 --> 05:11.458
12 WEEKS IN THE BIG APPLE.

05:11.470 --> 05:15.338
EVERYTHING'S
COMING UP PIZNARSKI.

05:19.380 --> 05:20.517
SHERIFF?

05:20.520 --> 05:22.442
VERONICA'S ON THE PHONE.

05:22.450 --> 05:24.441
THAN KS.

05:24.450 --> 05:26.452
Veronica: 95%.

05:26.460 --> 05:27.859
YOU PASSED.

05:27.860 --> 05:29.452
Yeah, I passed,

05:29.460 --> 05:31.621
AND I BEAT YOUR SCORE
BY 2 POINTS.

05:31.630 --> 05:33.120
BUT DON'T WORRY, DAD.

05:33.130 --> 05:35.894
I'LL STILL LOB IN THE TOKEN CALL
FROM TIME TO TIME

05:35.900 --> 05:39.097
asking for advice, thereby
validating your existence.

05:39.100 --> 05:40.260
HONEY?

05:40.270 --> 05:41.259
YEAH?

05:41.270 --> 05:43.761
I made a 97%.

05:45.070 --> 05:50.098
IT'S BENEATH YOU TO LIE TO ME
IN THIS, MY FINEST HOUR.

05:50.110 --> 05:51.202
Are you at your desk?

05:51.210 --> 05:52.199
NO.

05:52.210 --> 05:53.973
ARE YOU AT MY DESK?

05:55.920 --> 05:56.648
YES.

05:56.650 --> 05:58.242
Then this will be easy.

05:58.250 --> 05:59.717
PULL OUT MY MIDDLE DRAWER.

05:59.720 --> 06:02.655
I had a feeling
this moment would come.

06:02.660 --> 06:04.321
You see it there?

06:04.330 --> 06:06.059
YEP.

06:06.060 --> 06:08.722
Sweetie, maybe you should
go sit back down

06:08.730 --> 06:10.163
AT THE RECEPTIONIST'S DESK.

06:10.170 --> 06:13.367
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]
GOT TO GO. DUTY CALLS.

06:15.840 --> 06:19.059
MARS INVESTIGATIONS.
DETECTIVE MARS SPEAKING.

06:19.070 --> 06:22.608
Man: [ Ugandan accent ] Yes, I
believe I have discovered a son

06:22.610 --> 06:24.146
I never knew I had.

06:24.150 --> 06:27.517
OKAY, AND YOU'D LIKE US
TO TRACK THIS BOY DOWN?

06:27.520 --> 06:29.511
No, I know where he is.

06:29.520 --> 06:32.614
I want proof
he's, in fact, my son.

06:32.620 --> 06:37.683
His name is Apollo --
Apollo Bukenya.

06:37.690 --> 06:41.319
* A LONG TIME AGO,
WE USED TO BE FRIENDS *

06:41.330 --> 06:47.064
* BUT I HAVEN'T THOUGHT OF YOU
LATELY AT ALL *

06:47.700 --> 06:49.804
* COME ON, NOW, SUGAR *

06:49.810 --> 06:52.370
* BRING IT ON, BRING IT ON,
YEAH *

06:52.370 --> 06:55.874
* JUST REMEMBER ME WHEN *

06:55.880 --> 07:00.715
* WE USED TO BE FRIENDS
A LONG TIME AGO *

07:00.720 --> 07:02.984
* WE USED TO BE FRIENDS *

07:02.990 --> 07:06.551
-- Captions by VITAC --
www.vitac.com

07:09.760 --> 07:13.059
"THERE WAS NO STRUGGLE,
NO PROTEST, NO CRYING.

07:13.060 --> 07:16.029
"SHE JUST TOLD ME
TO GO WITH THE SOLDIERS.

07:16.030 --> 07:19.830
"I CAN'T IMAGINE HOW AFRAID
FOR ME SHE MUST HAVE BEEN.

07:19.840 --> 07:22.559
I NEVER
SAW MY MOTHER AGAIN."

07:24.070 --> 07:27.506
SO IMAGINE WHAT IT'LL MEAN
IF I CAN REUNITE HIM

07:27.510 --> 07:30.070
WITH THE FATHER
HE'S NEVER MET.

07:30.080 --> 07:32.241
WHAT?

07:32.250 --> 07:33.512
IT'S LIKE THE NBA.

07:33.520 --> 07:35.647
FATHERLESS BOY
MAKES GOOD,

07:35.650 --> 07:37.140
THE DOUGH STARTS ROLLING IN,

07:37.150 --> 07:41.382
AND HERE COMES LONG-LOST DADDY
EXPECTING A PAYDAY.

07:41.390 --> 07:42.618
IT'S NOT THE SAME THING.

07:42.630 --> 07:44.655
THE WORLD IS UPSIDE DOWN.

07:44.660 --> 07:46.753
VERONICA MARS
WANTS TO BELIEVE IN MIRACLES,

07:46.760 --> 07:47.988
AND I'M THE CYNICAL ONE.

07:48.000 --> 07:49.695
IT'S NOT LIKE
HE CAN LIE ABOUT IT.

07:49.700 --> 07:51.395
THERE WILL BE
A PATERNITY TEST.

07:51.400 --> 07:54.858
SO WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?
STEAL A DNA SAMPLE FROM APOLLO?

07:54.870 --> 07:56.804
KIZZA DOESN'T WANT ME
TO STEAL ANYTHING.

07:56.810 --> 07:59.108
HE DOESN'T EVEN WANT APOLLO
TOLD ABOUT THE POSSIBILITY

07:59.110 --> 08:01.203
UNTIL HE'S MORE CERTAIN
THEY'RE FATHER AND SON.

08:01.210 --> 08:02.871
SO HOW ARE YOU
SUPPOSED TO PROVE IT?

08:02.880 --> 08:05.098
HE E-MAILED ME A PDF
OF A LETTER HE HAS

08:05.110 --> 08:07.146
FROM A WOMAN HE CLAIMS
IS APOLLO'S MOTHER.

08:07.150 --> 08:09.914
SO IF I CAN GET A LOOK
AT ANYTHING APOLLO MIGHT HAVE

08:09.920 --> 08:11.717
WITH HIS MOM'S
HANDWRITING --

08:11.720 --> 08:13.312
MAYBE YOU CAN
MAKE MIRACLES HAPPEN.

08:13.320 --> 08:16.824
SO, HOW DOES IT FEEL
TO BE A PROFESSIONAL DETECTIVE?

08:16.830 --> 08:18.320
GREAT. [ CHUCKLES ]

08:18.330 --> 08:21.493
KNOW HOW MUCH I'M MAKING
ON MY FIRST PROFESSIONAL CASE?

08:21.500 --> 08:22.660
NADA.

08:22.670 --> 08:24.661
HE'S SCRAPED
JUST ENOUGH TOGETHER

08:24.670 --> 08:26.797
FOR A CHEAP PLANE TICKET
IF THE NEWS IS GOOD.

08:26.800 --> 08:29.360
HE HAD TO E-MAIL ME THE LETTER
FROM A KINKO'S.

08:29.370 --> 08:31.634
I HAVE TO WAIT ON HIS CALLS
FROM THE PAY PHONE

08:31.640 --> 08:33.107
IN HIS NEW YORK
BOARDINGHOUSE.

08:33.110 --> 08:35.601
YEAH, THAT'S NOT A GUY
LOOKING FOR A PAYDAY.

08:35.610 --> 08:37.703
TELL YOUR ROOM MATE
I CAME BY

08:37.710 --> 08:39.917
HOPING TO KILL TIME
BETWEEN CLASSES,

08:39.920 --> 08:42.741
GETTING TO SECOND BASE,
THEN LEFT UNSATISFIED.

08:42.750 --> 08:44.638
HE'S A GOOD GUY, VERONICA.

08:44.650 --> 08:47.187
TRY NOT TO RIP OUT
HIS HEART.

08:48.790 --> 08:50.655
Keith: TOMMY, I'M CURIOUS.

08:50.660 --> 08:52.287
HOW IS IT
THAT YOU FOUND YOURSELF

08:52.290 --> 08:54.827
IN POSSESSION OF JEWELRY
REPORTED STOLEN

08:54.830 --> 08:57.822
FROM TWO SEPARATE HOMES?

08:57.830 --> 08:59.491
THE OWNER OF BRODY'S PAWN

08:59.500 --> 09:02.833
SAID YOU WERE QUITE ANXIOUS
TO UNLOAD SAID MERCHANDISE.

09:02.840 --> 09:05.604
DON'T ANSWER THAT.

09:07.080 --> 09:09.537
CAN YOU TELL ME WHERE YOU WERE
TWO NIGHTS AGO

09:09.540 --> 09:10.677
BETWEEN 9:00 AND 11:00?

09:10.680 --> 09:12.272
DON'T ANSWER THAT.

09:12.280 --> 09:14.441
I WAS SO FOND OF YOU
WHEN I WAS A PRIVATE DETECTIVE.

09:14.450 --> 09:17.988
THEN YOU'LL UNDERSTAND WHY
YOU SHOULDN'T EXPECT MY VOTE?

09:17.990 --> 09:19.878
[ SIGHS ]

09:19.890 --> 09:22.484
THE BREAK-INS
WERE PROFESSIONAL JOBS --

09:22.490 --> 09:25.129
TOPFLIGHT SECURITY SYSTEMS
DISABLED.

09:25.130 --> 09:27.223
TRY NOT TO BE OFFENDED, TOMMY,
WHEN I SUGGEST

09:27.230 --> 09:29.767
THAT PERHAPS YOU ARE NOT
THE LEADER OF THE CREW.

09:29.770 --> 09:32.967
YOU MIND TELLING ME WHO IS?

09:32.970 --> 09:35.234
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
PUT ME BACK IN MY CELL,

09:35.240 --> 09:39.028
LET ME KNOW WHEN
THE BAIL BONDSMAN GETS HERE?

09:39.880 --> 09:43.202
ANXIOUS TO GET BACK
TO THE RIVER STYX, TOMMY?

09:43.210 --> 09:46.714
MR. SHAW HERE
WORKS WITH THE FITZPATRICKS.

09:46.720 --> 09:48.415
I GOT WHAT I NEEDED.

09:48.420 --> 09:51.787
DEPUTY, TAKE OUR FRIEND BACK
TO THE CELL HE ENJOYS SO MUCH.

09:51.790 --> 09:53.655
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

09:55.990 --> 09:58.424
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

09:58.430 --> 10:00.227
HI, APOLLO?

10:00.230 --> 10:01.959
UM, I'M VERONICA MARS.

10:01.960 --> 10:04.121
I'M A REPORTER FOR
THE HEARST FREE PRESS.

10:04.130 --> 10:05.927
WE MET AT YOUR
RADIO INTERVIEW,

10:05.930 --> 10:08.239
AND I'M HOPING
TO DO A STORY ON YOU, TOO.

10:08.240 --> 10:09.901
YOU WROTE THE BOOK

10:09.910 --> 10:12.367
SO PEOPLE WOULD KNOW
WHAT'S HAPPENING THERE.

10:12.370 --> 10:13.576
I KNOW.

10:13.580 --> 10:15.878
SURE. I'VE GOT SOME TIME
LATER TODAY.

10:15.880 --> 10:17.609
DOES THAT WORK FOR YOU?

10:17.610 --> 10:19.043
MM-HMM.

10:19.050 --> 10:21.814
MY POINT IS THAT WHITE FLOUR
IS ESSENTIALLY POISON.

10:21.820 --> 10:24.744
COUPLE WEEKS,
YOU'LL BE HOME EATING WITH US.

10:24.750 --> 10:26.286
YOU'LL FEEL LIKE
A NEW PERSON.

10:26.290 --> 10:29.157
I DON'T KNOW. I RELY PRETTY
HEAVILY ON MY MORNING BAGEL.

10:29.160 --> 10:31.958
WHICH IS EXACTLY WHY
YOU NEED TO BE WITHOUT IT.

10:31.960 --> 10:33.359
OH, AND I WAS ABLE
TO GET YOU

10:33.360 --> 10:35.920
THAT JOB IN THE MAILROOM
I WAS TELLING YOU ABOUT.

10:35.930 --> 10:37.966
PARKER. ELBOWS.

10:37.970 --> 10:40.359
IT'S ENOUGH FOR YOU
TO MAKE SOME SPENDING MONEY

10:40.370 --> 10:42.497
BEFORE WE LEAVE
FOR YOUR AUNT LOUISE'S.

10:42.500 --> 10:46.038
THANKS, DAD, BUT I WAS THINKING
OF LOOKING FOR A JOB,

10:46.040 --> 10:48.179
LIKE, AT A DAYCARE
OR SOMETHING.

10:48.180 --> 10:50.045
SO YOU CAN SPEND THE SUMMER
WITH A COLD

10:50.050 --> 10:52.109
AND RUIN EVERYONE'S VACATION?
I DON'T THINK SO.

10:52.110 --> 10:56.069
SO, LOGAN, WHAT SORT OF CAREER
ARE YOU PURSUING?

10:59.420 --> 11:01.980
[ British accent ]
OH, SORRY. WERE YOU ABOUT TO --

11:01.990 --> 11:02.979
YEAH.

11:02.990 --> 11:06.528
APOLLO,
YOU'VE GOT A VISITOR.

11:06.530 --> 11:07.758
HI.

11:07.760 --> 11:09.398
COME IN. TAKE A SEAT.

11:09.400 --> 11:12.767
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION
IN VIDEO GAME ]

11:16.040 --> 11:17.064
OH!

11:17.070 --> 11:18.901
PLEASE DON'T
LEAD YOUR STORY

11:18.910 --> 11:21.879
ON HOW I LIKE TO PLAY
"GRAND THEFT AUTO."

11:21.880 --> 11:24.542
MAKE ME SOUND
LESS FRIVOLOUS.

11:24.550 --> 11:26.177
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:27.820 --> 11:29.879
SOMETIMES
WE'D BE SENT ON WAVES

11:29.890 --> 11:32.757
WHERE THE TACTIC WAS
TO OVERPOWER OUR ENEMIES

11:32.760 --> 11:34.819
THROUGH SHEER
WEIGHT OF NUMBERS.

11:34.820 --> 11:37.357
WE WERE DIVIDED INTO TWO UNITS

11:37.360 --> 11:39.920
AND GIVEN DRUGS
TO READY US TO FIGHT.

11:39.930 --> 11:41.955
I WOULD MAKE MYSELF
VOMIT UP THE DRUGS,

11:41.960 --> 11:43.359
THEN CONVINCE
THE TWO LEADERS

11:43.370 --> 11:46.225
I WAS GOING TO BE
IN THE OTHER'S UNIT.

11:46.230 --> 11:48.630
INSTEAD,
I'D HIDE IN THE BUSH

11:48.640 --> 11:51.438
AND BLEND IN
WITH THE RETURNING FIGHTERS.

11:51.440 --> 11:55.331
TO STAY ALIVE,
ONE HAD TO THINK QUICKLY.

11:55.340 --> 11:57.103
WHAT'S THAT
"SURVIVOR" SLOGAN?

11:57.110 --> 12:00.944
"OUTWIT, OUTPLAY, OUTLAST"?

12:00.950 --> 12:03.418
I WAS A SURVIVOR.

12:05.990 --> 12:10.029
NOW, VERONICA,
DID YOU HAVE MORE QUESTIONS?

12:10.030 --> 12:11.725
UM...

12:11.730 --> 12:13.595
[ PAPER RUSTLES ]

12:13.600 --> 12:15.249
UH...

12:15.260 --> 12:20.163
LET'S TALK ABOUT THE DAYS
BEFORE YOUR CONSCRIPTION.

12:22.040 --> 12:24.258
Logan: I REALLY THINK
THEY LIKED ME.

12:24.270 --> 12:26.977
Parker: YEAH,
I DON'T REALLY THINK

12:26.980 --> 12:28.732
YOU SURVIVED THE GOOGLING.

12:28.740 --> 12:30.549
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:30.550 --> 12:32.677
[ GRUNTS ]

12:32.680 --> 12:34.318
[ SIGHS ]

12:34.320 --> 12:37.414
IS IT WRONG THAT I'D RATHER
BE TRAMPLED BY HORSES

12:37.420 --> 12:40.116
THAN SPEND THE SUMMER
WITH MY PARENTS?

12:40.120 --> 12:42.554
NO, THE HORSES
ARE A MUCH BETTER OPTION.

12:42.560 --> 12:43.879
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:43.890 --> 12:46.552
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT ELSE AM I GONNA DO?

12:46.560 --> 12:49.893
I DIDN'T SIGN UP FOR CLASSES
OR REQUEST ANY SUMMER HOUSING.

12:49.900 --> 12:52.289
YOU COULD STAY HERE.

12:53.170 --> 12:56.367
I'M SORRY.
I'M A LITTLE STUNNED.

12:56.370 --> 12:58.167
THAT IS SO SWEET.

12:58.170 --> 13:01.879
IT'S JUST -- MOVING IN,
THAT'S KIND OF A BIG STEP.

13:01.880 --> 13:03.279
OH, I MEANT
YOU COULD STAY HERE.

13:03.280 --> 13:05.009
I'LL BE GONE
MOST OF THE SUMMER,

13:05.010 --> 13:07.046
SO YOU'D HAVE THE WHOLE PLACE
TO YOURSELF.

13:07.050 --> 13:08.449
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

13:08.450 --> 13:11.783
GOING TO SOUTH AMERICA
TO SERVE WITH DICK.

13:11.790 --> 13:13.451
FOR THE WHOLE SUMMER?

13:13.460 --> 13:15.189
YOU WERE GOING HOME
TO DENVER.

13:15.190 --> 13:18.057
YEAH, WHICH IS
A TWO-HOUR FLIGHT FROM HERE.

13:18.060 --> 13:20.995
I THOUGHT
WE'D SEE EACH OTHER.

13:21.000 --> 13:22.456
I'M SORRY.

13:22.460 --> 13:25.167
I'VE BEEN PLANNING THIS THING
WITH DICK FOR A WHILE.

13:25.170 --> 13:26.762
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHERE WE'RE AT

13:26.770 --> 13:29.238
IF YOU'RE NOT GONNA SEE ME
AND THAT'S COOL WITH YOU.

13:29.240 --> 13:32.004
IT'S NOT COOL WITH ME.
I JUST DIDN'T THINK ABOUT IT.

13:33.280 --> 13:36.909
IT'S A SURF TRIP, PARKER.
IT HAS NOTHING TO DO WITH US.

13:36.910 --> 13:38.104
[ SIGHS ]

13:38.110 --> 13:40.214
Apollo:
THE DAY I WAS KIDNAPPED,

13:40.220 --> 13:43.212
MY MOTHER COULDN'T REALLY
PUT UP A FIGHT FOR ME

13:43.220 --> 13:45.313
WITHOUT RISKING
OTHERS' LIVES.

13:45.320 --> 13:48.187
BUT LATER THAT NIGHT,
SHE CAME TO THE CAMP

13:48.190 --> 13:51.682
TO BEG MY CAPTORS
TO GIVE ME BACK TO HER.

13:51.690 --> 13:53.191
I WASN'T THERE.

13:53.200 --> 13:55.657
THIS IS JUST WHAT
MY BEST FRIEND, JAMES, TOLD ME.

13:55.660 --> 14:01.838
AND WHEN THEY SAW
THAT JAMES KNEW MY MOTHER,

14:01.840 --> 14:05.332
THEY MADE HIM SHOOT HER.

14:09.840 --> 14:12.400
I'M SO SORRY.

14:15.120 --> 14:16.712
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

14:16.720 --> 14:18.608
DO YOU HAVE ANYTHING
FROM HER --

14:18.620 --> 14:22.989
PICTURES, PERSONAL ITEMS,
MEMENTOS?

14:22.990 --> 14:25.982
THE DAY I WAS CAPTURED,

14:25.990 --> 14:29.096
MY MOTHER SENT ME
TO THE MARKET.

14:30.500 --> 14:34.869
I CARRIED THE SHOPPING LIST
IN MY POCKET FOR YEARS.

14:34.870 --> 14:37.509
DO YOU STILL HAVE IT?

14:41.810 --> 14:44.040
[ SIGHS ]

14:50.350 --> 14:53.649
DO YOU MIND IF I MOVE
INTO BETTER LIGHT?

15:06.100 --> 15:08.034
A PERFECT MATCH.

15:14.280 --> 15:17.078
YOU'RE SURE THIS DOESN'T
BOTHER YOU TO TALK ABOUT?

15:17.080 --> 15:19.344
POSITIVE.

15:19.350 --> 15:21.739
LOGAN'S GOING SURFING
IN SOUTH AMERICA

15:21.750 --> 15:23.115
FOR THE WHOLE SUMMER.

15:23.120 --> 15:24.985
NEVER MENTIONED IT.
THE WHOLE SUMMER.

15:24.990 --> 15:26.048
WHAT IS THAT?

15:26.050 --> 15:27.358
IS THAT HOW HE IS,

15:27.360 --> 15:29.988
OR IS THAT JUST HOW HE IS
WITH ME?

15:29.990 --> 15:34.097
IT'S KIND OF JUST...
HOW HE IS.

15:34.100 --> 15:37.319
WHY IS THAT
NOT MORE COMFORTING?

15:39.200 --> 15:43.159
SO, MAC'S NOT AROUND
TO TALK ABOUT THIS STUFF?

15:43.170 --> 15:47.209
MAC'S FALLEN INTO THE BLACK HOLE
OF NEW LOVE.

15:47.210 --> 15:49.508
SHE ONLY COMES UP FOR AIR.

15:51.010 --> 15:52.477
HOW YOU GUYS DOING?

15:52.480 --> 15:55.677
I'M WEARING A DIFFERENT SHIRT,
JUST SO YOU KNOW.

15:55.680 --> 15:56.669
UH-HUH.

15:56.680 --> 15:58.443
KEEP IT.

15:58.450 --> 15:59.986
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

16:01.960 --> 16:03.427
[ SIGHS ]

16:03.430 --> 16:05.227
I HAVE TO,
HAVE TO, HAVE TO

16:05.230 --> 16:07.289
GO TO MY MORNING CLASSES
TOMORROW.

16:07.300 --> 16:10.224
GETTING LOST IN
THE SEX-NAP-EAT-REPEAT LOOP.

16:10.230 --> 16:12.892
I'M IN THE PORN VERSION
OF "GROUNDHOG DAY."

16:12.900 --> 16:14.367
"POUNDHOG DAY"?

16:14.370 --> 16:17.635
WHEN'S THE LAST TIME
YOU WENT TO CLASS?

16:17.640 --> 16:19.062
UH, FEBRUARY.

16:19.070 --> 16:20.401
ARE YOU KIDDING?

16:20.410 --> 16:21.775
BUSINESS
HAS BEEN BOOMING.

16:21.780 --> 16:24.669
MY CLASSES HAVE KIND OF
FALLEN BY THE WAYSIDE.

16:24.680 --> 16:28.047
SO NOW BEGINS
THE 11th-HOUR CRAM SESSION.

16:28.050 --> 16:29.677
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO,
I'M DONE.

16:29.680 --> 16:32.319
THE COUNTDOWN TO MY EXPULSION
HAS BEGUN.

16:32.320 --> 16:35.915
FRANKLY, IT'S LIBERATING.
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:35.920 --> 16:37.649
MMM.

16:40.730 --> 16:42.493
[ SIGHS ]

16:49.440 --> 16:52.307
YOU WERE JUST WAITING FOR ME
TO START PULLING OUT BOOKS?

16:52.310 --> 16:53.732
NO, I'M JUST BROWSING.

16:53.740 --> 16:56.436
BONING UP ON YOUR
SOUTH AMERICAN CULTURE?

16:56.440 --> 16:59.409
CONVERSATIONAL PORTUGUESE,
PERHAPS?

16:59.410 --> 17:01.446
IF YOU'RE GONNA BE
THAT CLOSE TO RIO --

17:01.450 --> 17:04.180
HOW DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT MY TRIP?

17:04.190 --> 17:06.044
PARKER MENTIONED IT.

17:08.090 --> 17:09.648
DID MY FAN CLUB
MEET TODAY?

17:09.660 --> 17:12.379
THOUGHT YOU GUYS
ONLY MET ON WEDNESDAYS.

17:12.390 --> 17:15.621
LOOK, SHE WAS BUMMED YOU DIDN'T
TELL HER ABOUT THE TRIP.

17:15.630 --> 17:18.622
AND YOU TOOK TURNS STICKING PINS
IN YOUR LOGAN DOLLS?

17:18.630 --> 17:23.602
NO, I TOLD HER
THAT'S JUST HOW YOU ARE.

17:32.450 --> 17:35.214
CRACK HER OPEN.
WE'RE CELEBRATING.

17:35.220 --> 17:37.347
I WAS OFFERED
ANOTHER INTERNSHIP.

17:37.350 --> 17:40.319
PEOPLE ARE JUST FALLING ALL OVER
THEMSELVES TO NOT PAY YOU.

17:40.320 --> 17:41.514
IT'S A GOOD FEELING.

17:41.520 --> 17:44.284
SO, THIS ONE
IS AT A RADIO STATION --

17:44.290 --> 17:47.498
KRAC, RIGHT HERE
IN NEPTUNE.

17:49.360 --> 17:51.669
IT'S NOT GLAMOROUS
AS THE PITCHFORK GIG,

17:51.670 --> 17:54.833
AND IT'S TOP 40,
WHICH MAKES MY PARTS HURT,

17:54.840 --> 17:56.137
BUT IT'S RADIO.

17:56.140 --> 17:58.631
I DON'T KNOW.
PITCHFORK IS MUSIC I'M INTO.

17:58.640 --> 18:01.734
IT'S NEW YORK,
WHICH IS GOOD...

18:02.810 --> 18:04.141
...AND BAD.

18:06.110 --> 18:07.247
LIKE, IN THE LONG RUN?

18:07.250 --> 18:09.548
I WANT TO BE IN RADIO.

18:09.550 --> 18:13.042
THEN YOU SHOULD TAKE WHATEVER
INTERNSHIP WILL GET YOU THERE.

18:13.050 --> 18:14.756
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

18:15.990 --> 18:17.389
HELLO?

18:17.390 --> 18:21.759
KIZZA, GOOD NEWS.
CAN YOU CATCH THE RED-EYE?

18:24.170 --> 18:26.161
[ BEEP ]

18:28.270 --> 18:29.862
HI, APOLLO, IT'S VERONICA.

18:29.870 --> 18:33.476
I'VE GOT SOMETHING ELSE
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT.

18:33.480 --> 18:35.277
Yeah, Veronica,
glad you called.

18:35.280 --> 18:36.804
I WANTED
TO TALK TO YOU, TOO.

18:36.810 --> 18:39.779
COULD YOU COME MEET ME
AT THE LIBRARY?

18:40.580 --> 18:45.449
SHERIFF MARS,
AS I LIVE AND BREATHE.

18:45.450 --> 18:48.283
LIAM.
THANKS FOR STOPPING BY.

18:48.290 --> 18:51.054
WELL, THE DEPUTY YOU SENT
ASKED SO POLITELY.

18:51.060 --> 18:52.550
PLEASE TAKE A SEAT.

18:52.560 --> 18:54.096
OKAY.

18:54.100 --> 18:55.692
LOOKS GOOD.

18:55.700 --> 18:59.192
I HAD ONE OF YOUR BOYS
IN HERE EARLIER -- TOMMY SHAW.

18:59.200 --> 19:00.565
HE WAS TRYING
TO UNLOAD GOODS

19:00.570 --> 19:03.164
STOLEN FROM THIS STRING
OF BURGLARIES.

19:03.170 --> 19:05.206
HOW IS TOMMY DOING
THESE DAYS?

19:05.210 --> 19:07.235
I DON'T THINK
I'VE SEEN THAT BOY

19:07.240 --> 19:09.379
SINCE HIS MOTHER'S WAKE
BACK IN '05.

19:09.380 --> 19:11.598
YOU'RE WORKING
ON A THIRD STRIKE, LIAM.

19:11.610 --> 19:14.477
YOU MIGHT CONSIDER
QUITTING WHILE YOU'RE AHEAD.

19:14.480 --> 19:16.710
KEITH, WE BOTH KNOW
MY TRIP DOWN HERE

19:16.720 --> 19:20.087
WOULDN'T HAVE BEEN VOLUNTARY
IF YOU HAD ANYTHING.

19:20.090 --> 19:21.557
NOTHING YET,

19:21.560 --> 19:24.154
BUT I'M GONNA KEEP
PICKING OFF YOUR FLUNKIES.

19:24.160 --> 19:25.559
EVENTUALLY, ONE OF THEM

19:25.560 --> 19:29.223
IS GONNA TRADE ME 10 YEARS
FOR YOUR NAME.

19:29.230 --> 19:30.663
AND A WORD OF CAUTION --

19:30.670 --> 19:33.389
DON LAMB'S NO LONGER
IN CHARGE HERE.

19:33.400 --> 19:36.198
YOU SPEAKING ILL
OF THE DEAD, KEITH?

19:36.200 --> 19:39.363
WOW, 'CAUSE,
FROM WHAT I UNDERSTAND,

19:39.370 --> 19:42.305
THIS CRIME WAVE
DOESN'T LET UP,

19:42.310 --> 19:45.643
YOU WON'T BE IN CHARGE
LONG EITHER.

19:48.520 --> 19:51.717
COURSE, MAYBE
THESE ROBBERIES WILL STOP

19:51.720 --> 19:56.111
IF I FIND OUT WHAT HAPPENED
TO KENDALL CASABLANCAS

19:56.120 --> 19:57.883
AND MY MONEY.

20:00.530 --> 20:03.522
KENDALL'S DEAD, AND I SUSPECT
YOUR BROTHER BURIED HER

20:03.530 --> 20:06.226
IN A SHALLOW GRAVE
IN THE DESERT.

20:06.230 --> 20:09.893
AS FOR THE MONEY,
IT WAS NEVER YOURS.

20:16.380 --> 20:19.144
WOULDN'T BOTHER UNPACKING.

20:19.150 --> 20:22.244
[ FOOTSTEPS DEPARTING ]

20:22.250 --> 20:25.811
Apollo: VERONICA,
GLAD YOU CAN MAKE IT.

20:25.820 --> 20:29.449
THERE'S SOMEONE
I WANT YOU TO MEET.

20:29.460 --> 20:33.453
THIS IS WILSON BEHAN,
EDITOR OF THE FREE PRESS.

20:33.460 --> 20:36.156
HE REQUESTED AN INTERVIEW.

20:36.160 --> 20:37.798
Wilson: HEY, VERONICA.

20:37.800 --> 20:41.190
I DON'T REMEMBER ASSIGNING YOU
TO DO A STORY ON APOLLO.

20:41.200 --> 20:42.497
[ SIGHS ]

20:46.070 --> 20:48.231
WELL...

20:48.240 --> 20:51.539
I'M GONNA LET YOU TWO
SORT THIS OUT.

20:56.520 --> 21:02.550
ALL RIGHT, I WASN'T ASSIGNED
TO YOU BY THE SCHOOL PAPER.

21:02.560 --> 21:05.757
THE TRUTH IS, I WORK
AS A PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR,

21:05.760 --> 21:10.424
AND I WAS HIRED BY A MAN
WHO BELIEVES HE'S YOUR FATHER.

21:12.300 --> 21:13.892
WHO IS HE?

21:13.900 --> 21:16.061
HIS NAME IS KIZZA ONEKO.

21:16.070 --> 21:18.334
HE HAD THIS.

21:21.510 --> 21:23.569
IT'S A LETTER TELLING KIZZA

21:23.580 --> 21:27.539
TO TAKE AN OPPORTUNITY
TO LEAVE UGANDA FOR AMERICA.

21:27.550 --> 21:29.541
THE WAR
HAD SEPARATED THEM.

21:29.550 --> 21:30.847
KIZZA SAYS HE LEFT

21:30.850 --> 21:33.614
NOT KNOWING YOUR MOTHER
WAS PREGNANT.

21:33.620 --> 21:35.952
RECOGNIZE THE HANDWRITING?

21:35.960 --> 21:39.179
THE GROCERY LIST
I SHOWED YOU --

21:39.190 --> 21:40.748
MY HOMETOWN PAPER
PRINTED IT.

21:40.760 --> 21:43.661
THIS KIZZA PERSON
SIMPLY FORGED THIS.

21:43.670 --> 21:48.460
WE'LL PROVE HIS PATERNITY
ONE WAY OR THE OTHER

21:48.470 --> 21:50.097
WITH A BLOOD TEST.

21:50.100 --> 21:52.830
NO, WE WON'T.

21:58.780 --> 22:02.011
IT'S NOT THE ETHICS OF WHAT MAX
IS DOING THAT BOTHERS ME.

22:02.020 --> 22:04.284
AT LEAST I CAN
RATIONALIZE THAT AWAY,

22:04.290 --> 22:06.542
'CAUSE I HAD IT
FILED AWAY IN MY HEAD

22:06.550 --> 22:08.154
AS A COLLEGE LARK --

22:08.160 --> 22:10.754
A UNIQUE WAY FOR A PHILOSOPHY
MAJOR TO MAKE SOME EXTRA CASH.

22:10.760 --> 22:13.456
IN ITS OWN WAY, IT SHOWED
ALL THESE QUALITIES I ADMIRE.

22:13.460 --> 22:15.894
HE'S DEDICATED,
HE'S GOT A KEEN BUSINESS SENSE,

22:15.900 --> 22:18.494
AND, LET'S FACE IT,
HE'S GOOD AT WHAT HE DOES.

22:18.500 --> 22:20.639
HELPS PEOPLE CHEAT.

22:20.640 --> 22:23.029
YEAH, THAT. [ SIGHS ]

22:23.040 --> 22:25.804
BUT TODAY, WHEN HE SAID
HE WAS FLUNKING OUT OF SCHOOL

22:25.810 --> 22:28.472
AND HE WAS JUST GONNA GET
AN OFF-CAMPUS APARTMENT

22:28.480 --> 22:29.731
AND KEEP DOING WHAT HE DOES,

22:29.740 --> 22:31.776
IT WAS LIKE LOOKING
INTO A CRYSTAL BALL,

22:31.780 --> 22:33.509
AND I DIDN'T LIKE
WHAT I SAW.

22:33.520 --> 22:34.839
WHAT DID YOU SEE?

22:34.850 --> 22:36.909
ME FALLING COMPLETELY
IN LOVE WITH HIM,

22:36.920 --> 22:39.912
LOSING ALL REASON,
ENDING UP HOSTING CANDLE PARTIES

22:39.920 --> 22:42.514
AND SELLING FAMILY HEIRLOOMS
ON eBay.

22:42.520 --> 22:45.250
I HAVE THE POTENTIAL
TO GO DOWN THAT ROAD.

22:45.260 --> 22:46.659
NO, YOU DON'T.

22:46.660 --> 22:49.026
I DO. LOVE MAKES ME LAZY.
IT'S A DANGEROUS DRUG.

22:49.030 --> 22:51.828
KILLS MORE BRAIN CELLS
THAN CRYSTAL METH.

22:51.830 --> 22:54.037
HOW'S YOUR CELL COUNT
THESE DAYS?

22:54.040 --> 22:56.167
HMM, I CAN STILL
DO LONG DIVISION,

22:56.170 --> 22:59.059
BUT I CAN'T QUITE REMEMBER
ALL THE CONTINENTS.

22:59.070 --> 23:02.278
SO PIZNEYLAND IS
THE HAPPIEST PLACE ON EARTH?

23:02.280 --> 23:03.406
HAPPY ENOUGH.

23:03.410 --> 23:04.968
THERE'S NO ROLLER COASTER,

23:04.980 --> 23:08.279
BUT I THINK I CAN DO WITHOUT
THE ADRENALINE AND NAUSEA.

23:08.280 --> 23:10.009
HMM.

23:10.020 --> 23:11.578
HI, IT'S VERONICA MARS.

23:11.590 --> 23:13.808
I'M TRYING
TO TRACK DOWN APOLLO.

23:13.820 --> 23:16.152
I'VE LEFT SEVERAL MESSAGES
ON HIS CELLPHONE.

23:16.160 --> 23:18.879
OH, I'M SORRY.
YEAH, HE HASN'T BEEN AROUND.

23:18.890 --> 23:20.721
ANY IDEA
WHERE HE MIGHT BE?

23:20.730 --> 23:22.152
Olympia's, maybe?

23:22.160 --> 23:24.890
YOU KNOW WHO MIGHT KNOW
IS ZEKE MOLINDA.

23:24.900 --> 23:27.368
He's one of the guys from
the African Student Alliance.

23:27.370 --> 23:30.089
Oh, wait, I don't think
they're even speaking anymore.

23:30.100 --> 23:32.898
They had some sort
of falling-out.

23:32.910 --> 23:34.969
UH, HAVE YOU CHECKED
WITH DR. TONIN?

23:34.980 --> 23:37.369
I mean, she's practically
his mum.

23:37.380 --> 23:39.871
THAT'LL GET ME STARTED.

23:39.880 --> 23:41.711
THAN KS. BYE.

23:41.720 --> 23:43.711
YOU MUST BE KIZZA.

23:43.720 --> 23:47.554
YES, UH, I'M LOOKING
FOR DETECTIVE MARS.

23:47.560 --> 23:48.913
I'M DETECTIVE MARS.

23:48.920 --> 23:52.754
YOU'RE JUST A GIRL.
YOU'RE A TEENAGER.

23:52.760 --> 23:54.921
A GIRL, A TEENAGER,
AND A PRIVATE DETECTIVE.

23:54.930 --> 23:57.353
I'M A TRIPLE THREAT.
BARELY FITS ON MY BUSINESS CARD.

23:57.360 --> 24:00.796
YOU ARE THE PERSON WHO'S
ARRANGING A MEETING WITH MY SON?

24:00.800 --> 24:03.769
I AM. UNFORTUNATELY,
YOUR SON ISN'T AS AVAILABLE

24:03.770 --> 24:05.237
AS I THOUGHT HE WOULD BE.

24:05.240 --> 24:08.073
I'M HAVING A LITTLE TROUBLE
LOCATING HIM RIGHT NOW,

24:08.080 --> 24:09.707
BUT I HAVE SEVERAL LEADS.

24:17.490 --> 24:19.014
WE'VE BEEN
PRETTY VOCAL SUPPORTERS

24:19.020 --> 24:20.658
OF YOUR CANDIDACY,
KEITH.

24:20.660 --> 24:22.082
IT'S BECOMING
MORE DIFFICULT.

24:22.090 --> 24:24.581
THERE ARE OTHERS
AT THE HOMEOWNERS ASSOCIATION

24:24.590 --> 24:26.729
SUGGESTING WE SHOULD BRING IN
MR. VAN LOWE,

24:26.730 --> 24:28.721
SEE WHAT HE'S ALL ABOUT.

24:28.730 --> 24:31.528
I APPRECIATE
THE HEADS UP, CARL.

24:31.530 --> 24:32.792
I THINK WE'RE
ON THE RIGHT TRACK,

24:32.800 --> 24:34.336
BUT IT MAY TAKE SOME TIME.

24:34.340 --> 24:36.968
THE ELECTION'S IN TWO WEEKS.
YOU DON'T HAVE TIME.

24:36.970 --> 24:39.564
HERE'S THE DATA
YOU ASKED FOR, KEITH.

24:41.940 --> 24:45.273
WHAT KIND OF HOME-SECURITY
SYSTEM YOU GOT, CARL?

24:45.280 --> 24:46.508
SAFEHOUSE.

24:46.510 --> 24:48.546
YOU MIGHT
WANT TO REPLACE IT.

24:50.950 --> 24:53.111
HEY, CAN WE TALK
FOR A SECOND?

24:53.120 --> 24:54.257
I HAVE A CLASS.

24:54.260 --> 24:56.387
I DON'T WANT TO
GET INTO A WHOLE THING.

24:56.390 --> 24:57.823
THERE'S NO WHOLE THING.

24:57.830 --> 25:01.027
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT THE SURF TRIP.

25:01.030 --> 25:02.349
FINE.

25:02.360 --> 25:04.089
KISSING IS CH EATING,

25:04.100 --> 25:07.695
AND WHAT I DON'T KNOW
WILL HURT ME.

25:07.700 --> 25:09.759
YOU SHOULD COME WITH ME.

25:09.770 --> 25:12.705
YOU WANT ME TO COME
TO SOUTH AMERICA

25:12.710 --> 25:14.234
WITH YOU AND DICK?

25:14.240 --> 25:17.107
I MEANT IT WHEN I SAID
THAT I DIDN'T THINK ABOUT

25:17.110 --> 25:19.977
BEING AWAY FROM YOU
FOR THREE MONTHS.

25:19.980 --> 25:21.345
NOW I HAVE.

25:21.350 --> 25:25.184
I HAVE TO PROCESS THINGS.
IT'S JUST WHAT I'M LIKE.

25:25.190 --> 25:27.852
OH, MY GOD! [ LAUGHS ]

25:34.260 --> 25:36.592
OLYMPIA, YOU WOULDN'T
HAPPEN TO KNOW

25:36.600 --> 25:38.261
WHERE I MIGHT FIND APOLLO?

25:38.270 --> 25:39.760
I KNOW HE'S AVOIDING YOU.

25:39.770 --> 25:43.763
VERONICA, I THINK HE SHOULD
MEET THE GUY, GET TESTED.

25:43.770 --> 25:46.637
IF I SEE HIM AGAIN,
I'LL KEEP WORKING ON HIM.

25:48.210 --> 25:49.837
I WISH I COULD HELP YOU.

25:49.840 --> 25:53.173
TO TELL YOU THE TRUTH,
I'M STARTING TO WORRY ABOUT HIM.

25:53.180 --> 25:56.570
WILL YOU LET ME KNOW
IF YOU FIND HIM?

26:07.090 --> 26:08.455
HI, ZEKE?

26:08.460 --> 26:09.927
[African accent ]
YES.

26:09.930 --> 26:12.194
I'M VERONICA. I'M TRYING TO FIND
APOLLO BUKENYA.

26:12.200 --> 26:13.895
YOU'RE LOOKING
IN THE WRONG PLACE.

26:13.900 --> 26:15.697
WE DON'T TALK ANYMORE.

26:15.700 --> 26:18.828
I HEARD.
THIS IS KIND OF LAST-DITCH.

26:18.840 --> 26:20.364
SORRY TO BOTHER YOU.

26:20.370 --> 26:23.771
WHAT DO YOU NEED HIM FOR?

26:25.480 --> 26:27.641
I'M DOING A STORY ON HIM.

26:29.250 --> 26:31.844
IN THAT CASE,
I'VE GOT YOUR LEAD.

26:31.850 --> 26:34.580
HE DIDN'T WRITE
"SOLDIER OF MISFORTUNE."

26:34.590 --> 26:36.182
HIS ADVISER DID.

26:36.190 --> 26:39.227
HE KNOWS IT,
AND HE KNOWS I KNOW IT.

26:40.860 --> 26:43.897
SO APOLLO TOLD HIS ADVISER
THE STORY OF HIS LIFE,

26:43.900 --> 26:45.322
AND SHE WROTE THE BOOK?

26:45.330 --> 26:46.888
NOT EXACTLY.

26:46.900 --> 26:49.630
THE STORIES IN APOLLO'S BOOK
ARE TRUE FOR MANY OTHERS.

26:49.640 --> 26:52.006
THEY SIMPLY
DIDN'T HAPPEN TO HIM.

26:52.010 --> 26:54.672
HE WAS NEVER CONSCRIPTED.

27:02.380 --> 27:04.712
ZEKE WAS APOLLO'S ROOMMATE
FRESHMAN YEAR.

27:04.720 --> 27:07.086
HE SAYS APOLLO TOLD HIM
ALL ABOUT HIS LIFE,

27:07.090 --> 27:09.615
BUT UNTIL "SOLDIER
OF MISFORTUNE" CAME OUT,

27:09.620 --> 27:10.951
NEVER INCLUDED ANYTHING

27:10.960 --> 27:13.622
ABOUT BEING A CHILD SOLDIER
IN THE LRA.

27:13.630 --> 27:16.292
SO WHAT SHOULD I DO?

27:18.670 --> 27:21.798
I DON'T KNOW. NOTHING?

27:21.800 --> 27:23.461
I'M SERIOUS, VERONICA.

27:23.470 --> 27:26.667
IT'S A FACT THAT THERE ARE
CHILD SOLDIERS IN AFRICA.

27:27.310 --> 27:30.131
THERE'S THIS ORGANIZATION,
INVISIBLE CHILDREN,

27:30.140 --> 27:32.643
THAT SENDS VOLUNTEERS
OVER TO UGANDA

27:32.650 --> 27:34.914
TO HELP
PROTECT THE KIDS THERE.

27:34.920 --> 27:36.569
THEY HAVE A BOOTH UP
AT THE JOB FAIR.

27:36.580 --> 27:39.811
THERE WAS A CROWD AROUND IT
TODAY ABOUT FIVE PEOPLE DEEP.

27:39.820 --> 27:41.788
I THINK
I'M MISSING THE POINT.

27:41.790 --> 27:44.725
EVERYONE IS THERE
BECAUSE OF APOLLO'S BOOK.

27:44.730 --> 27:46.459
IF YOU EXPOSE HIS BOOK
AS A HOAX,

27:46.460 --> 27:48.928
I PROMISE YOU'LL BE KILLING
A LOT MORE

27:48.930 --> 27:50.693
THAN HIS LITERARY CAREER.

27:50.700 --> 27:52.691
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

27:52.700 --> 27:55.533
[ SIGHS ]

27:55.540 --> 27:56.962
HELLO?

27:56.970 --> 27:58.506
Veronica,
hi, it's Olympia.

27:58.510 --> 28:01.206
I just saw Apollo.
He's heading back to his room.

28:01.210 --> 28:03.906
I think
he's ready to talk.

28:07.920 --> 28:09.911
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

28:10.820 --> 28:13.038
WHAT ABOUT THE FIRST CHECK?

28:13.050 --> 28:15.257
BUT I'VE ALREADY --

28:15.260 --> 28:18.149
SO THEY'RE JUST GONNA
PULL THE PLUG, JUST LIKE THAT?

28:18.160 --> 28:20.720
FINE, FINE.

28:20.730 --> 28:22.527
I HAVE LAWYERS, TOO.

28:22.530 --> 28:24.361
[ CLICK ]

28:25.970 --> 28:28.939
SORRY.
IS THIS A BAD TIME?

28:28.940 --> 28:30.669
NO. NO, NOW IS FINE.

28:30.670 --> 28:33.833
JUST GIVE ME A SECOND TO TAKE
MY LAUNDRY OUT OF THE MACHINE

28:33.840 --> 28:35.774
BEFORE SOMEONE STEALS IT.

28:35.780 --> 28:37.941
I CAN WAIT.

28:39.710 --> 28:42.110
"PULL THE PLUG,"
LAWYERS, CHECKS?

28:42.120 --> 28:46.784
TO WHOM, PRAY TELL, WAS
THE YOUNG MR. BUKENYA SPEAKING?

28:53.060 --> 28:55.255
_ Woman:
Silver Pictures.

28:55.260 --> 28:57.251
LOOKS LIKE
"SOLDIER OF MISFORTUNE"

28:57.260 --> 29:00.468
WON'T BE COMING
TO A THEATER NEAR YOU.

29:05.770 --> 29:08.136
THIS MAN WHO CLAIMS
TO BE MY FATHER --

29:08.140 --> 29:10.734
OLYMPIA CONVINCED ME.
I WANT TO MEET HIM.

29:10.740 --> 29:12.401
I'LL TAKE THE BLOOD TEST.

29:12.410 --> 29:13.946
I'LL ARRANGE IT.

29:15.620 --> 29:18.088
Mr. Casablancas:
HELLO, SON.

29:20.790 --> 29:22.109
DAD?

29:22.120 --> 29:23.826
WHAT, THEY JUST
LET YOU IN MY ROOM?

29:23.830 --> 29:25.457
WELL, I AM PAYING FOR IT,
AFTER ALL.

29:25.460 --> 29:28.952
I THOUGHT HUNDREDS OF SAPS
WHO INVESTED IN YOUR COMPANY

29:28.960 --> 29:30.257
WERE PAYING FOR IT.

29:30.260 --> 29:32.399
I FEEL BETTER ABOUT MYSELF
ALREADY.

29:32.400 --> 29:35.392
I, UH...

29:35.400 --> 29:37.095
I TURNED MYSELF IN.

29:37.100 --> 29:39.466
MY LAWYER MADE
ALL THE ARRANGEMENTS.

29:39.470 --> 29:43.031
I HAVE A COUPLE MONTHS
BEFORE MY INCARCERATION.

29:43.040 --> 29:44.541
TIRED OF RUNNING, DICK.

29:44.550 --> 29:47.439
I WANT TO PAY MY DEBT TO SOCIETY
AND GET IT OVER WITH.

29:47.450 --> 29:50.248
AND WHAT KIND OF DEBT
DID YOUR LAWYER NEGOTIATE?

29:50.250 --> 29:52.445
A YEAR.
[ CHUCKLES ]

29:52.450 --> 29:55.453
THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT THIS BIKER
I WENT TO HIGH SCHOOL WITH GOT

29:55.460 --> 29:57.758
FOR STEALING THE HUNTINGTON'S
LAWN JOCKEY.

29:57.760 --> 29:59.921
IT'S GOOD
TO BE THE KING, HUH?

30:02.030 --> 30:03.895
I'LL CONSIDER
OUR SOCIETAL FLAWS

30:03.900 --> 30:07.028
DURING MY YARD TIME
IN THE BIG HOUSE.

30:08.800 --> 30:10.199
[ SIGHS ]

30:10.200 --> 30:12.361
I TURN MYSELF IN
AT THE END OF AUGUST.

30:12.370 --> 30:16.409
AT LEAST WE HAVE A FEW MONTHS
BEFORE THEN.

30:16.410 --> 30:18.571
I'VE RENTED A ROOM
A COUPLE FLOORS DOWN.

30:18.580 --> 30:21.344
I WANT TO SPEND AS MUCH TIME
AS POSSIBLE WITH YOU.

30:21.350 --> 30:23.671
I'M GONNA BE GONE
MOST OF THE SUMMER.

30:23.680 --> 30:25.341
I'M GOING
ON THIS SURF TRIP.

30:25.350 --> 30:27.386
SURF TRIP?
I'M GOING TO JAIL, DICK.

30:27.390 --> 30:29.119
I KNOW. I'M SORRY.
I JUST --

30:29.120 --> 30:31.327
THIS IS THE ONLY CHANCE YOU HAVE
TO BE WITH YOUR FATHER,

30:31.330 --> 30:33.548
AND YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT
A SURF TRIP?!

30:34.900 --> 30:37.425
SILVER PICTURES?
WHAT IS SILVER PICTURES?

30:37.430 --> 30:39.819
IT'S A COMPANY
THAT MAKES MOVIES.

30:39.830 --> 30:44.108
MY POINT IS,
THERE'S NOT GOING TO BE A MOVIE

30:44.110 --> 30:45.737
OF "SOLDIER OF MISFORTUNE."

30:45.740 --> 30:48.573
THERE'S NOT GOING TO BE
A BIG CHECK.

30:48.580 --> 30:53.199
I SUSPECT OPRAH MAY TEAR APOLLO
A NEW ONE ON NATIONAL TV.

30:53.210 --> 30:54.518
WHAT DOES OPRAH
HAVE TO DO WITH --

30:54.520 --> 30:56.943
MR. ONEKO,
IF YOU TRACKED DOWN APOLLO

30:56.950 --> 30:59.817
IN HOPES OF FINDING
FINANCIAL SECURITY,

30:59.820 --> 31:02.288
I'M URGING YOU
TO SIMPLY WALK AWAY.

31:02.290 --> 31:06.386
HE NEEDS PEOPLE AROUND HIM
WHO CARE ABOUT HIM.

31:06.390 --> 31:08.392
IF THAT'S NOT YOU,
I CAN'T LET --

31:08.400 --> 31:11.392
MISS MARS, HAD IT NOT BEEN
FOR THE WAR,

31:11.400 --> 31:14.858
I NEVER
WOULD HAVE LEFT UGANDA.

31:14.870 --> 31:16.428
I CAME TO NEW YORK,

31:16.440 --> 31:20.661
A PLACE WHERE I HAD
NO FRIENDS, NO FAMILY,

31:20.670 --> 31:22.900
AS A MEANS OF SURVIVAL.

31:22.910 --> 31:24.343
I'M STILL ALIVE,

31:24.350 --> 31:27.444
BUT I'VE BEEN ALONE
FOR 21 YEARS.

31:29.050 --> 31:30.847
I DRIVE A CAB.

31:30.850 --> 31:35.458
I GO TO SCHOOL,
I PAY MY BILLS,

31:35.460 --> 31:36.688
BUT I AM LONELY.

31:36.690 --> 31:40.649
IF THIS IS MY SON,
PLEASE LET ME BE THERE

31:40.660 --> 31:44.266
TO COMFORT HIM
IN THIS DIFFICULT TIME.

31:56.710 --> 31:59.042
I DON'T THINK HE'S COMING.

32:01.050 --> 32:03.041
HE'LL BE HERE.

32:05.350 --> 32:08.251
YOU EVER NOTICE HOW THE STAINED
WOOD AROUND THE WINDOW

32:08.260 --> 32:10.581
HAS THE EFFECT
OF SHRINKING THE SPACE?

32:10.590 --> 32:12.785
I'M THINKING SOMETHING
MORE OF AN EGGSHELL

32:12.790 --> 32:14.326
WOULD REALLY
OPEN IT UP IN HERE.

32:14.330 --> 32:15.957
I SHOULD PROBABLY
WRITE THAT DOWN.

32:15.960 --> 32:17.621
ANYWAY, WHAT CAN I
DO FOR YOU, KEITH?

32:17.630 --> 32:19.598
I DON'T SUPPOSE, VINNIE,
YOU'VE NOTICED,

32:19.600 --> 32:21.739
BUT THERE'S
A CRIMINAL ELEMENT IN TOWN

32:21.740 --> 32:24.664
THAT WOULD REALLY LOVE
TO SEE YOU AS SHERIFF.

32:24.670 --> 32:26.661
OH, WHAT CAN I SAY?

32:26.670 --> 32:28.069
I'M A WALKING
BIG-10 PARTY.

32:28.080 --> 32:30.105
MUST BE WHY THE GIRLS
FROM THE SECRETARIAL POOL

32:30.110 --> 32:31.668
GAVE ME THAT NICKNAME.

32:31.680 --> 32:35.514
WHAT DO YOU KNOW ABOUT
SAFEHOUSE SECURITY SYSTEMS?

32:35.520 --> 32:36.578
HEY, SACKSY,

32:36.580 --> 32:39.378
MIND RUNNING OUT
AND GETTING A LATTE?

32:39.390 --> 32:41.858
I CAN HAVE HIM GET YOU
SOMETHING, AS WELL.

32:41.860 --> 32:43.487
SAFEHOUSE?

32:43.490 --> 32:45.458
YEAH, I DID SOME
CONSULTING WORK FOR THEM.

32:45.460 --> 32:49.089
DID YOU KNOW THAT ALL SEVEN
HOMES THAT HAVE BEEN BURGLARIZED

32:49.100 --> 32:50.328
SUBSCRIBE TO SAFEHOUSE?

32:50.330 --> 32:53.163
[ WHISTLES ]
QUITE A COINKYDINK.

32:53.170 --> 32:54.660
YOU AND THE FITZPATRICKS

32:54.670 --> 32:58.333
ARE THE PRIME BENEFICIARIES
OF THOSE ROBBERIES.

32:58.340 --> 33:00.137
I THINK YOU'RE
COLLUDING WITH THEM.

33:00.140 --> 33:01.778
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:01.780 --> 33:06.843
WELL, KEITH, YOU ARE CERTAINLY
ENTITLED TO YOUR THEORY.

33:06.850 --> 33:08.977
QUESTION IS...

33:08.980 --> 33:11.540
CAN YOU PROVE IT?

33:14.560 --> 33:16.050
[ FINGERS SNAP ]

33:17.560 --> 33:19.448
IT'S BEEN AN HOUR.

33:19.460 --> 33:21.257
[ SIGHS ]

33:21.260 --> 33:23.558
I'M SO SORRY, APOLLO.

33:23.560 --> 33:24.891
SORRY FOR WHAT?

33:24.900 --> 33:29.439
I EXPECT NOTHING,
SO I'M RARELY DISAPPOINTED.

33:35.680 --> 33:38.672
SO, DID YOU
TELL THIS KIZZA PERSON

33:38.680 --> 33:40.045
THAT I'M A FRAUD

33:40.050 --> 33:42.177
AND THAT I WON'T BE
COMING INTO MONEY

33:42.180 --> 33:45.183
AS ALL THE ARTICLES SAY?

33:45.190 --> 33:49.980
I TOLD HIM THERE WAS
THAT POSSIBILITY.

33:49.990 --> 33:52.151
GOOD.

33:55.030 --> 33:56.793
THANK YOU.

33:56.800 --> 33:59.394
YOU DID YOUR PART.

34:03.140 --> 34:05.199
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
MY PART?

34:05.210 --> 34:07.428
"SOLDIER OF MISFORTUNE" --

34:07.440 --> 34:10.432
THE STORY IS MINE.
I WROTE EVERY WORD OF IT.

34:10.440 --> 34:14.319
I NEEDED TO KNOW WHETHER THIS
KIZZA GENTLEMAN WOULD SHOW

34:14.320 --> 34:18.017
REGARDLESS OF MY STATURE
AND FINANCIAL SITUATION.

34:18.020 --> 34:21.183
SO, EVERYTHING
I TOLD HIM WAS --

34:21.190 --> 34:22.782
DISIN FORMATION --

34:22.790 --> 34:26.851
A PLAN TO SEPARATE
THOSE I CAN TRUST

34:26.860 --> 34:28.999
FROM THOSE I CAN'T --

34:29.000 --> 34:31.195
A PLAN
LIKE SO MANY OTHERS.

34:31.200 --> 34:34.897
ZEKE IS ACTUALLY
A VERY GOOD FRIEND OF MINE.

34:34.900 --> 34:36.936
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

34:36.940 --> 34:38.567
TAKE CARE.

34:41.940 --> 34:43.703
MARS INVESTIGATIONS.

34:43.710 --> 34:46.941
Veronica, why is there
a detainee in my jail

34:46.950 --> 34:48.542
NAMED KIZZA ONEKO

34:48.550 --> 34:51.713
WHO ASKS FOR HIS ONE PHONE CALL
TO BE MADE TO YOU?

34:51.720 --> 34:53.244
APOLLO, WAIT.

34:53.250 --> 34:55.150
WHY IS HE BEING DETAINED?

34:55.160 --> 34:56.479
HE WAS PICKED UP
DRIVING A RENTAL

34:56.490 --> 34:58.526
WITH PLATES
FROM A STOLEN CAR.

35:01.030 --> 35:02.429
[ DOOR OPENS ]

35:08.840 --> 35:10.831
APOLLO.

35:10.840 --> 35:12.569
MR. ONEKO,

35:12.570 --> 35:16.028
I'M HAPPY WE HAVE THIS CHANCE
TO MEET.

35:16.040 --> 35:18.201
AS AM I.

35:18.210 --> 35:20.747
OVERJOYED, IN FACT.

35:22.220 --> 35:24.211
I'M NOT SURPRISED
YOUR MOTHER NAMED YOU

35:24.220 --> 35:25.687
FOR THE GOD OF MUSIC.

35:25.690 --> 35:28.750
SHE HAD A BOOK OF MYTHOLOGY
THAT SHE TREASURED.

35:33.390 --> 35:36.496
I...I REMEMBER IT WELL.

35:36.500 --> 35:39.890
IT IS THE BOOK SHE USED
TO TEACH ME HOW TO READ.

35:45.310 --> 35:47.460
[Voice breaking ]
FATHER?

35:58.520 --> 36:01.011
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO HEAR ABOUT YOUR MOTHER

36:01.020 --> 36:04.456
AS THE YOUNG GIRL
THAT I FELL IN LOVE WITH?

36:10.300 --> 36:13.463
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

36:19.310 --> 36:21.107
YOU SURE
YOU WANT TO DO THIS?

36:21.110 --> 36:25.740
IT'S QUITE A COMMITMENT,
AND AFRICA'S A LONG WAY AWAY.

36:25.750 --> 36:27.638
I'M POSITIVE.

36:27.650 --> 36:28.810
OKAY.

36:31.320 --> 36:33.345
[ KEYBOARD KEYS CLICKING ]

36:33.350 --> 36:35.580
[ KNOCK ON DOOR,
DOOR OPENS ]

36:35.590 --> 36:39.048
I COME WITH TALES
FROM THE OUTSIDE WORLD.

36:39.060 --> 36:41.153
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:41.160 --> 36:44.266
OH, AND, UM,
I BROUGHT THESE FOR YOU.

36:44.270 --> 36:46.363
I WAS PASSING THROUGH
THE JOB FAIR,

36:46.370 --> 36:49.259
AND, UM, APPARENTLY,
THERE ARE CAREERS

36:49.270 --> 36:51.363
THAT A PHILOSOPHY DEGREE
PREPARES YOU FOR,

36:51.370 --> 36:55.636
SO JUST THOUGHT I'D GRAB THEM,
JUST IN CASE.

36:55.640 --> 36:58.108
I GUESS WE NEED TO
TALK ABOUT THIS, HUH?

36:58.110 --> 37:00.977
YEAH, MAYBE.

37:00.980 --> 37:02.413
HERE'S THE THING.

37:02.420 --> 37:08.188
I MAKE ABOUT $1,500 A WEEK
DOING SOMETHING I LIKE.

37:08.190 --> 37:10.613
I'M GONNA BE DOING THIS
FOR A WHILE.

37:10.620 --> 37:14.397
NOT FOREVER,
BUT FOR A WHILE.

37:14.400 --> 37:16.721
I HOPE THAT DOESN'T
CHANGE THINGS FOR YOU.

37:16.730 --> 37:22.088
I WISH THAT IT DIDN'T,
BUT IT KIND OF DOES.

37:22.100 --> 37:24.534
WELL, THAT SUCKS.

37:24.540 --> 37:28.670
YEAH, BUT I'M NOT SURE
HOW MUCH IT CHANGES THINGS.

37:28.680 --> 37:31.706
I WANT US
TO KEEP SEEING EACH OTHER.

37:33.310 --> 37:34.914
WELL, GREAT.

37:34.920 --> 37:37.912
JUST CAN'T DO THE BLISSFUL
LOVE-SHACK THING ANYMORE.

37:37.920 --> 37:42.050
I NEED TO GET BACK TO MY
REGULARLY SCHEDULED LIFE.

37:42.060 --> 37:43.618
IS THAT COOL?

37:43.620 --> 37:47.124
SO, DO YOU HAVE TO GET BACK
TO REALITY NOW OR...

37:47.130 --> 37:49.428
[ CHUCKLES ] NO.

37:49.430 --> 37:52.160
NO, I GOT A COUPLE HOURS.

37:52.170 --> 37:53.694
GOOD.

37:54.230 --> 37:56.835
[ LAUGHING ]

37:57.970 --> 38:00.803
[ SNORTING ]

38:04.240 --> 38:07.038
AAHl [LA
. UG
AAH! HS]

38:07.050 --> 38:08.677
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

38:12.990 --> 38:14.412
SON?

38:14.420 --> 38:15.910
JUST SO YOU KNOW,

38:15.920 --> 38:18.684
THE WORLD DOESN'T STOP
BECAUSE YOU DECIDED TO SHOW UP.

38:18.690 --> 38:21.056
HAD I KNOWN IT WAS INTERFERING
WITH YOUR SURFING,

38:21.060 --> 38:22.254
I WOULD HAVE COME SOONER.

38:22.260 --> 38:23.727
LIKE MAYBE
FOR CASSIDY'S FUNERAL?

38:23.730 --> 38:26.028
THIS IS WHERE HE DIED,
YOU KNOW?

38:26.030 --> 38:28.590
I WALK BY THE SPOT
HE SPLATTERED ON EVERY DAY.

38:28.600 --> 38:30.431
YOU THINK I'M NOT SORRY
ABOUT CASSIDY?

38:30.440 --> 38:33.500
WHAT ARE YOU SORRY FOR, DAD?
THAT HE'S DEAD?

38:33.510 --> 38:35.068
OF COURSE.

38:35.080 --> 38:37.969
YOU EVER THINK THAT HE KILLED
THOSE PEOPLE BECAUSE OF US?!

38:37.980 --> 38:39.345
WE USED TO HAVE CONTESTS

38:39.350 --> 38:40.908
TO SEE WHICH ONE OF US
COULD MAKE HIM CRY!

38:40.910 --> 38:43.071
I CAN BARELY
LIVE WITH MYSELF SOMETIMES,

38:43.080 --> 38:45.878
AND IT'S SO MUCH EASIER
WHEN YOU'RE NOT AROUND!

38:48.660 --> 38:51.652
Logan: HEY, LISTEN,
ABOUT OUR SUMMER PLANS,

38:51.660 --> 38:54.788
I KNOW YOU'RE GONNA THINK
THIS IS UNCOOL, BUT I KIND OF --

38:54.800 --> 38:56.722
I CAN'T GO.

38:56.730 --> 38:57.856
WHAT?

38:57.860 --> 38:59.191
YEAH, THE TRIP'S
NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

38:59.200 --> 39:00.724
MY DAD'S BACK,

39:00.730 --> 39:04.291
WANTS ME TO SPEND TIME WITH HIM
BEFORE HE GOES TO JAIL.

39:04.300 --> 39:06.734
I GET IT, MAN.

39:06.740 --> 39:10.471
SORRY FOR SCREWING UP
YOUR SUMMER, YOU KNOW?

39:15.020 --> 39:16.271
HEY!

39:16.280 --> 39:18.339
I WAS JUST GONNA CALL YOU.

39:18.350 --> 39:21.148
I TOLD MY PARENTS.
THEY FREAKED OUT.

39:21.150 --> 39:23.118
IT WAS THE BEST FEELING.

39:23.120 --> 39:25.588
WHAT'S WRONG?

39:27.190 --> 39:28.919
THE TRIP'S OFF.

39:28.930 --> 39:32.263
DICK'S DAD
CAME BACK INTO TOWN,

39:32.270 --> 39:35.899
AND NOW HE CAN'T GO, SO...

39:35.900 --> 39:38.232
OH.

39:38.240 --> 39:40.333
SO...

39:40.340 --> 39:44.470
I GUESS WE'RE NOT
GOING, THEN?

39:44.480 --> 39:47.108
HE WAS FOOTING
HALF THE BILL FOR THE HOUSE,

39:47.110 --> 39:49.249
AND IT'D JUST BE
REALLY EXPENSIVE.

39:49.250 --> 39:54.244
AND IT WAS A THING ME AND DICK
WERE PLANNING ON TOGETHER.

39:54.250 --> 39:56.252
I UNDERSTAND.

39:56.260 --> 39:58.080
YEAH.

39:58.090 --> 40:02.550
I GUESS I'M GOING
TO DENVER THEN.

40:05.400 --> 40:07.197
Veronica:
DAD, CHECK THIS OUT.

40:07.200 --> 40:09.839
I'M VINCENT VAN LOWE.

40:09.840 --> 40:10.659
AW, NO.

40:10.670 --> 40:12.433
I WAS BORN IN NEPTUNE.

40:12.440 --> 40:13.862
I LIVE IN NEPTUNE.

40:13.870 --> 40:16.202
MY FRIENDS AND FAMILY
LIVE IN NEPTUNE.

40:16.210 --> 40:20.579
THAT'S WHY WHAT HAPPENS IN OUR
CITY CONCERNS ME SO MUCH.

40:20.580 --> 40:22.775
THERE'S NOTHING MORE IMPORTANT

40:22.780 --> 40:24.589
THAN THE SAFETY
OF OUR CHILDREN...

40:24.590 --> 40:26.683
VINNIE HAS KIDS?
NONE THAT HE'S AWARE OF.

40:26.690 --> 40:30.251
...AND THE SECURITY
OF OUR HOMES.

40:30.260 --> 40:33.957
I'M VINCENT VAN LOWE,
AND I'M ASKING FOR YOUR VOTE.

40:33.960 --> 40:35.825
Man: VINNIE VAN LOWE
HAS BEEN ENDORSED

40:35.830 --> 40:37.695
BY THE NEPTUNE
HOMEOWNERS ASSOCIATION.

40:37.700 --> 40:41.739
WELL, FROM THE RIDICULOUS
TO THE SUBLIME,

40:41.740 --> 40:45.005
APOLLO AND KIZZA'S BLOOD TEST
CHECKED OUT.

40:45.010 --> 40:46.261
NO SURPRISE.

40:46.270 --> 40:48.773
